FBIS4-60516 "drnes102dd_94017" FBIS-NES-94-102 Daily Report 26 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Suha 'Arafat Denies Rumors of Impending Divorce Suha 'Arafat Denies Rumors of Impending Divorce NC2605065594 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 0515 GMT 26 May 94 NC2605065594 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] Suha 'Arafat will not revert to [her maiden name] Suha Tawil. 'Arafat and I will remain together until death do us part. With these words, the wife of Palestinian leader Yasir 'Arafat denied rumors of her intention to divorce following differences with her husband over the arrest of her maternal uncle, who was detained for five days and then released after he was interrogated on charges of squandering public funds.
